{"_type":"issue","id":"pdoc-1gf","title":"Review: multi-format-export pre-flight","notes":"VERDICT (revised): approved.\n\nThe two major issues were fixed:\n- EPUB CSS class naming aligned across P2, P4, P5 to P3's canonical paper-* kebab-case form (pdoc-cbr, pdoc-4wn, pdoc-1e9 reopened, edited, reclosed).\n- EPUB stylesheet path corrected: P2 OEBPS/styles.css → OPS/styles/paper.css. Other OEBPS strings also removed.\n\nVerification (post-fix):\n- grep 'pd-callout|pd-code|pd-action|pd-section|pd-chip|OEBPS/' P2 → 0\n- grep 'pd-' P4 → 0\n- grep 'pf-callout|pf-code|pf-action|pf-section|pf-chip' P5 → 0\n- paperflow-validate P2/P3/P4/P5 all ok:true (zero Mermaid failures across 11 blocks)\n- P2 now contains illustrative Word style names (CalloutSuccessSubtle, ActionPrimaryMedium, SectionCompact, CodeDarkNormal) for spot-check parity with P3.\n\nMinor issues 3, 4, 5, 6 from the original verdict are NOT addressed in this fix (P6 missing docs-page + changelog tasks; P6 dropped P2's UUID-strategy open question; P2 illustrative styles partially addressed via the spot-check anchor). These are deferred to the build-phase /paperflow:plan invocation that materializes B1-B10. Logged here for that planner to pick up.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-18T20:28:06Z","created_by":"pelle","updated_at":"2026-05-18T20:38:11Z","closed_at":"2026-05-18T20:38:11Z","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["goal-multi-format-export"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"pdoc-1gf","depends_on_id":"pdoc-0r1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-18T22:28:06Z","created_by":"pelle","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"pdoc-1gf","depends_on_id":"pdoc-ap9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-05-18T22:28:06Z","created_by":"pelle","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
