{"_type":"issue","id":"pdoc-3f4","title":"Export Papir docs to Word, Pages, Google Docs, and EPUB with style fidelity","description":"Export Papir docs to Word, Pages, Google Docs, and EPUB with style fidelity.\n\nBOUND DECISIONS (grill resolved 2026-05-18 — recommendations accepted as-is):\n 1. Mechanism: pandoc-wasm in-browser\n 2. Format set v1: DOCX + EPUB (strict)\n 3. Round-trip: one-way only for v1\n 4. EPUB version: EPUB 3 with EPUB 2 backwards-compatible structure (nav.xhtml + ncx.xml)\n 5. Converter location: browser-first (in-Papir export button), CLI second-class\n 6. reference.docx authoring: hybrid — code generates styles.xml from variant mapping; designer polishes in Word\n 7. Variant fidelity: exact 1:1 mapping (every variant → named Word style)\n 8. Edge case default: warning callout in exported doc (no silent drop, no abort)\n 9. Export UI: single export button with format dropdown\n10. Async vs sync: sync (wasm is fast)\n11. Test fixture: one exhaustive + per-variant regressions (both)\n12. CI: parse-and-assert primary; visual diff as --visual flag","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-05-18T19:47:11Z","created_by":"pelle","updated_at":"2026-05-18T20:38:18Z","closed_at":"2026-05-18T20:38:18Z","close_reason":"All children completed","labels":["goal-multi-format-export"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
